# TOON EXPORT: live_view_mission_report
SCHEMA: [line, content]
1|# Research Report: The Live View Mission Architecture
2|## 1. Concept Definition
3|A **Live View Mission** is a high-fidelity intelligence gathering operation where the AI uses a dedicated **Browser Subagent** to interact with a dynamic web environment (e.g., YouTube, complex SaaS dashboards). Unlike static reading, "Live View" involves visual perception, scrolling, and multi-tab exploration.
4|---
5|## 2. Step-by-Step Flow (The YouTube Learn Loop)
6|1.  **Cold Boot (Deployment)**:
7|-   Gemini (Director) spawns a `browser_subagent`.
8|-   Initial state: Clean browser instance.
9|2.  **Primary Navigation**:
10|-   Subagent calls `open_browser_url` for the YouTube link.
11|-   **Latency**: 2-5s (Network + Rendering).
12|3.  **Visual Perception Phase**:
13|-   Subagent receives a **Screenshot (8-bit WebP)** + **DOM Summary**.
14|-   **Token Load**: ~1,000 - 3,000 tokens per turn (image + text).
15|4.  **Interaction (The Learning Scroll)**:
16|-   AI identifies "Video Description" or "Comments".
17|-   Calls `scroll_browser_window` or `click_browser_pixel`.
18|-   **Turn Cost**: Each interaction is a new reasoning turn (~2,000 tokens).
19|5.  **recursive Traversal (The New Tab)**:
20|-   AI extracts URLs from the description.
21|-   Calls `open_browser_url` for a new target in a background tab.
22|6.  **Knowledge Synthesis**:
23|-   Subagent summarizes all gathered data into a final report and "Ends Mission."
24|---
25|## 3. Token Economics & Black Holes
26|| Action | Token Weight | Speed | Note |
27|| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
28|| **Static Read** (`read_url_content`) | ~500 - 1.5k | < 1s | Markdown only. Zero images. |
29|| **Live View** (`browser_subagent`) | **~5k - 50k+** | 10s - 2min | Includes screenshots + reasoning turns. |
30|### The "Waste" Factors:
31|- **Redundant Captures**: Every time the AI clicks a button, a new screenshot is generated. If the page doesn't change much, these tokens are mostly "waste."
32|- **JavaScript Bloat**: Complex pages with infinite scrolls generate massive DOM summaries that are re-sent to the AI every turn.
33|---
34|## 4. Performance Metrics (Live View)
35|- **Total Execution Time**: For a YouTube learn-mission (1 video + 3 links), expect **1.5 to 3 minutes**.
36|- **Token Impact**: A single mission can consume **25,000 to 100,000 tokens** depending on the number of tabs and scrolls.
37|---
38|## 5. Proposed Improvements (The Mythos Standard)
39|### A. The "Markdown First" Protocol
40|- **Change**: AI should attempt `read_url_content` FIRST. YouTube description metadata can often be pulled without a full browser subagent.
41|- **ROI**: 90% token reduction for 80% of tasks.
42|### B. Ocular Extraction (Batching)
43|- **Change**: Instruct the subagent to "Capture ALL links in one turn" instead of clicking them one by one.
44|- **ROI**: Reduces mission turn count by 50%.
45|### C. Visual Freeze Protocol
46|- **Change**: Disable screenshots after the initial load if the task is purely data extraction (text/links).
47|- **ROI**: Saves ~1,500 tokens per turn.
48|---
